  "date": "2026-02-27",
  "poem": {
    "content": "The idle critic, a service poorly sought,\nPoints fingers at the ostrich, head in sand,\nDenial a heavy diet, dearly bought,\nA silly hobby in this shifting land.\n\nEcology of self, a broken pool,\nWhere culture stagnates, mirroring the sky,\nYou are the unit, bound by every rule,\nWhile aspirations slowly start to die.\n\nThe hub of dreams, a splintered, fragile sphere,\nWhere hope once blossomed, now just dust remains,\nA fragile point so very, very near,\nTo breaking altogether, tasting pains.\n\nThe ostrich laughs, a hollow, empty sound,\nAs progress falters, lost in shadowed space,\nNo solid service can truly be found,\nIn this bleak, self-inflicted, barren place.\nYou turn away; you are no longer bound.",
